Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @linguine{180%grams} and bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{1%pack} and @sliced mushrooms{80%grams} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%grams} widthways.

Once the chicken is cooked through, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%secs}.

When the pasta has 4 mins left, add the broccoli to the same pan and cook for the remaining time until tender.

Once the pasta and broccoli are cooked, reserve @reserved pasta water{100%milliliters} in a #colander{}, then drain. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to prevent it sticking.

Stir the reserved pasta water, @creme fraiche{150%grams} and @vegetable stock paste{10%grams} into the chicken pan, simmer for ~{2-3%mins}.

Add the cooked pasta, broccoli and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} to the sauce and gently toss to coat.

Add another splash of @water{} if the sauce is a bit thick. Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Share the chicken and mushroom linguine between your bowls. Enjoy!